remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding pixel data to the WebP image format,
including both single-frame and animated WebP output. Use
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.Encode(SkiaSharp.SKPixmap,SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions)>
for single images or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame},SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions)>
for animated sequences.

This class has no instance state and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
using var bitmap = new SKBitmap(200, 200);
using var canvas = new SKCanvas(bitmap);
canvas.Clear(SKColors.CornflowerBlue);

var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = SKWebpEncoderOptions.Default;

using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
if (data != null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
